ADULTS
WITH
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
THE
MAIN
CHARACTERISTIC
OF
PATIENTS
WITH
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
IS
LUNG
INVOLVEMENT
THE
FATAL
OUTCOME
OF
THE
DISEASE
IS
MOST
OFTEN
DUE
TO
PULMONARY
COMPLICATIONS
SINCE
THE
PAPER
BY
WEST
ET
AL
1954
ON
PULMONARY
FUNCTION
IN
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
THE
